Packages that use DataMapper
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.api.mappers These Mappers allow a developer to programmatically define the connection between persistent objects and the database 
org.sakaiproject.genericdao.springjdbc These spring jdbc based generic DAO implementations can either be used directly to handle persistent object operations in an application or extended to meet more specific needs.

          Set all required settings for running the DAO, can be used in the cases where using the complete constructor is inconvenient
This does not actually start the DAO, run JdbcGenericDao.startup() to start it
Note that this will be started automatically by Spring if this is created as a Spring bean, no actions are necessary and setting an init method is not needed
